         <div type="transcription">
            <fw type="leafNum" corresp="#lf">(–)7</fw>
            <p>
<lb corresp="#a1"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>l<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/></w><gap reason="plain" quantity="2"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a2"/><w>täṣne</w><num value="15">10-5</num><w>mā</w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a3"/><w>ṅ<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>e</w><w>yā</w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b1"/><w>ṣmä</w><gap reason="plain" quantity="5"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<w><supplied>la</supplied><lb corresp="#b2"/>p</w><w>wipäsmāṃ</w><w>ane</w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b3"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>sä</w><w>s<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>āṃ</w><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><gap reason="lost"/></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... which ... 15 ... not ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... is to sit down (?) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... shaking [one's] head ... inside ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">In one frame with <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a408k"/>-<ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a408r"/>. The left margin is preserved. Although this fragment is not edited by <bibl><title corresp="ref:ogihara2009"/></bibl>, I think that <hi>täṣne</hi> directly preceding a number (see also <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a408o"/> a1) can also be taken as an indication that this fragment belongs to the Bhikṣuṇī-Prātimokṣasūtra. Further, line b2 seems to be parallel to <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-tht322"/> b1, b2 (Ilya Itkin, p.c.). Therefore, it is assumed that it belongs to manuscript A 415-416, not to A 406-408.</note><note corresp="#b1" type="philcomment"><distinct type="ms_text">[_ṣ]_m_a</distinct>: the next akṣara could be <distinct type="ms_text">_l</distinct>; a restoration <hi>ṣmä(l)</hi> is possible. A 3sg.prs. <hi>ṣmä(ṣ)</hi> is less likely.</note><note corresp="#b2" type="philcomment"><hi>(la)p wipäsmāṃ ane</hi>: This line seems to be parallel to <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-tht322"/> b1, b2, which would imply that <hi>wipäsmāṃ</hi> means 'shaking', not 'making wet', as I suggested in August 2012. I owe this new interpretation and the restoration to <hi>(la)p</hi> to Ilya Itkin (p.c., 14 April 2015).</note></p>
         </div>
